The paper discusses a novel application of Locality Sensitive Hashing (LSH) to seismic data, which involves processing large amounts of time series data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science), and cs.SE (software engineering). However, given the focus on data-driven science and the use of domain knowledge to optimize the analysis pipeline, cs.DB and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely given the specific focus of the paper.
